The memorandum is a delegation of authority from President Joseph R. Biden Jr. to the Secretary of State regarding the Child Soldiers Prevention Act of 2008. The Secretary of State is delegated the authority to waive the prohibition on providing Foreign Military Financing and Excess Defense Articles to Rwanda and Turkey, and to make the necessary determinations and certifications for such waivers. The Secretary of State is also authorized to notify the appropriate congressional committees of the waivers and their justifications, as well as to publish the determination in the Federal Register.